James Bridle contra el optimismo digital: James Bridle on digital optimism: the urgency of rethinking our use of technology
El año pasado aparecieron varios estudio: Last year, several studies appeared revealing the outrageous amount of water consumed by data centres dedicated to artificial intelligence. Twelve months later, we are still missing a study that determines the volume of energy consumed by the torrential amount of books that are being written and published about this technology.
Ironías aparte, y revisando la lista de: Ironies aside, and looking at the list of new non-fiction books being presented this year at the Frankfurt Book Fair, it is surprising that all the new books from publishers such as MIT are focused in unison on analysing any detail of AI from unexpected angles. One is aware of the decisive potential of AI to change many dimensions of our existence. That does not prevent there being such an objectively inflated editorial fecundity about artificial intelligence -Harari included- that we run the risk of obscuring the valuable reflection of the opportunistic text.
